acteristic forenames:  Hungarian Laszlo, Zoltan, Geza, Istvan, Gabor, Miklos, Tibor, Arpad, Denes, Imre, Attila.","German (Bavaria, Tyrol): from Middle High German <i>pap</i> ‘baby food’, Dutch <i>pap</i> ‘porridge, pap’, hence perhaps a nickname denoting someone who had lost his teeth or subsisted on a meager diet.","Hungarian: from <i>pap</i> ‘priest (of the Catholic or Orthodox Church)’, probably an occupational name for someone in the service of a priest or a nickname for a pious person. This surname is also found in Romania and Slovakia, and also among Rusyns. Compare   Pap   and   Pop  ."]}]},{"name":"Adam","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Ukrainian (standard transliteration <b>Adamovych</b>) and Belorussian: patronymic from the personal name   Adam  .","Americanized form of Serbian and Croatian <b>Adamović</b>, Slovak <b>Adamovič</b>, cognates of 1 above."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Jenken","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Transferred use of the surname, which is derived from the medieval given name <i>Jankin</i>. This was a pet form of the boy's name   Jan  , with the diminutive suffix <i>-kin</i>. The modern given name is popular in Wales, where the surnames <i>Jenkin</i> and <i>Jenkins</i> are common."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Jenken Ap Adam was born in 1301, in England, United Kingdom, his father, Adam Ap Reginald, was 26 and his mother, Christian Verch Gwaring, was 24. He married Gwenlian Verch Aron in 1326, in Monmouthshire, Wales, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1344, in Monmouthshire, Wales, United Kingdom, at the age of 43."},"et":{"1301–1344":"1301–1344","1301–1377":"1301–1377","1305–1332":"1305–1332","1327–1377":"1327–1377","1275–1307":"1275–1307","1277–1365":"1277–1365","1327":"1327","1305":"1305","1326":"1326","1301":"1301","1344":"1344","13